						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">miker00lz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> I'll use your tip of defaulting to 44100. That's CD quality anyway.</div><br />It might be audibly worse if your sound synthesis has aliasing. At a higher rate, you effectively offload some of the filtering to the OS/sound card/human ears. The title music in Kid Icarus stresses filtering.</div>

