orce the emu to pause on losing focus anyway. That's actually caused me to get killed in games a handful of times if another window decides to pop up, or i accidentally hit the Windows key. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />I'm doing a bit more work on the code. I didn't get enough time to work on it yet, so tomorrow I'll definitely come back and upload with some fixes. I may or may not need tips with some of the audio bugs, not sure yet. Damn NES sound hardware is so quirky.</div>

